items.title: Asian travel platform Klook is filing for a New York IPO
items.description: Klook revealed that it generated $417.1 million in revenue in 2024, a 24% increase. Yet the company isn’t profitable, losing $99.3 million last year.

items.title: Air Force veteran says cybersecurity is a natural career transition for civilian life—and it’s a field with more than 500,000 open jobs
items.description: A veteran has been trained to think like an adversary, says Air Force veteran Frankie Sclafani.

items.title: Warren Buffett admits his Giving Pledge philanthropy was not ‘feasible’—he’s instead left his three kids $500 million a year to give away
items.description: The Berkshire Hathaway billionaire says his longevity has led to “unavoidable consequences” for his charitable objectives.

items.title: New York City business leaders are split on whether to relocate their firms to avoid Mayor-elect Zohran Mamdani’s policies
items.description: None have announced definitive plans to do so, but some business leaders say they’re considering moving out.
